:::summary
Ancient Greek is one of the oldest and most influential languages in Western history. It is the language of Homer's epics, Plato's philosophy, and — most crucially for Christians — the New Testament. Koine ("common") Greek was the *lingua franca* of the Mediterranean world during the time of Jesus Christ, and studying Greek opens direct access to the words of Jesus, Paul, and the Apostles as originally recorded.
